Rating: 3
I would rate this recipe 3 1/2 forks. After making it a few times it narrowed it down to this; wash and DRY the chicken well. Add salt and pepper to some flour and lightly dust the chicken in the flour. Fry in HOT oil/butter as recommemded. Brown chicken throughly all over then remove from pan. Pour off some, but not all, of the fat, leaving 2-3 Tbls. Brown your carrots and onions very well, until they are golden. Triple the amount of wine and broth mixture, add some finely chopped herbs such as sage and rosemary, and let the mixture cook down, without the chicken. (I found that I would get a crisp skin on the chicken only to have it get soggy fromo the continued simmering of the broth) Once the wine/stock mixture is thickened and tasty, add the chicken pieces and cook for only 5-10 minutes more, uncovered. P.S. I added canned artichoke hearts and fingerling potatoes to the simmering broth in the last 15-20 minutes. As for whether the chicken is done or not, if you thorougly brown the chicken in the beginning it really doesn't need any more that that.

