Fabulous! A definite keeper. The only change we made was using dried thyme and a 'California' bay leaf. Served with a small salad this is a perfect meal for any occasion.

Rating: 4
I used non-fat sour cream in the recipe. And substituted Jarlsburg cheese. I also used fresh baby onions. And, the chicken we used was skinned and boned. Because of these changes, I don't know what it was supposed to taste like, but the result was fabulous. The sauce is rich, but not too rich, and was appreciated by the adults and children alike.

Rating: 4
Superb indeed! In answer to the previous reviewer who wondered how to make the recipe without the creme fraiche, I intended to add it but completely forgot - and it turned out perfectly without it. Also, I used fresh pearl onions instead of frozen. Also, I used lowly California bay leaves and the boneless, skinless breasts I had on hand and it was devine nonetheless. Alongside, I served aspargus and hollandaise sauce(using the recipe from the same issue) and a salad of baby greens with lemony poppyseed vinaigrette (from the Silverpalate cookbook). Definitely a keeper.

