Rating: 4
This is a lovely and lively version of a french classic, one we will keep. As for it's richness, well, as we say in the South, "No cross, no crown." However, luckily the legs and thighs are more forgiving than the breasts and ca be browned without their skin. Keep the creme fraiche and strip the meat. (But save the skins for stock.)

